  <description type="morphology">Plants mainly 10–20 dm, not spiny. Leaves narrowly oblanceolate, to oblanceolate, often thickened, 12–25(–30) × 2–5 mm, apex mainly rounded. Pistillate flowers borne in panicles mostly 5–25 cm. Fruiting bracteoles on stipes 0–2 mm, body typically with 4 prominent, laciniate wings extending length of bract, united throughout, 6–10(–15) × 8–11(–15) mm, apex toothed, surface of wings and body smooth or reticulate.</description>
